+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_018VvS6Cd1UyzhXDKwYADkTq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01WyVeJ4wSCa9cjeyShCRRXP","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"OUTPUT=$(gemini -p \"Implement a beam propagation simulator in a single file src/index.ts for a TypeScript ESM project (ES2022 target, strict mode).\n\nRequirements:\n1. Export function countBeamCells(grid: string[][]): number - counts distinct cells visited by any beam\n2. Export function countBeamPaths(grid: string[][]): bigint - counts total distinct source-to-exit paths using bigint\n3. Grid cells: 'S' = beam source (top row, emits beam straight down), '^' = splitter, '.' = empty\n4. Beam from source moves straight down (row+1, same col)\n5. When a beam hits a splitter '^', it splits into down-left (row+1, col-1) and down-right (row+1, col+1). Original beam is consumed.\n6. Unsplit beam continues in its current direction (down, down-left, or down-right)\n7. Beam is absorbed (stops) when it moves outside grid boundaries\n8. Multiple beams can occupy same cell simultaneously\n9. Splitters split regardless of incoming beam direction\n10. Source cell 'S' counts as visited. Splitter cells hit by beams count as visited.\n11. A path ends when beam exits the grid (moves beyond any edge). Absorbed beams that exit count as paths.\n\nAlgorithm for countBeamCells:\n- Use BFS/simulation. Track active beams as (row, col, direction) where direction is 0=down, -1=down-left, 1=down-right.\n- Start with beam at source position going down.\n- Use a Set of 'row,col' strings for visited cells. Mark source as visited.\n- For each beam: check current cell. If splitter, add two new beams (down-left, down-right from next step). If not splitter, continue in current direction.\n- Actually: start beam AT source. Mark source visited. Then step: compute next position. If out of bounds, beam dies. If in bounds, mark visited, check if cell is splitter -> spawn two beams with directions -1 and 1, otherwise continue same direction.\n\nAlgorithm for countBeamPaths:\n- MUST NOT enumerate paths (2^50 is too large). Use memoization on splitters.\n- For each splitter, compute pathsFromSplitter(splitter) = traceBeam(splitter.row+1, splitter.col-1, -1) + traceBeam(splitter.row+1, splitter.col+1, 1)\n- traceBeam(row, col, direction): follow the beam step by step. If it goes out of bounds, return 1n. If it hits a splitter, return pathsFromSplitter(that splitter) (memoized).\n- For the source: totalPaths = traceBeam(sourceRow+1, sourceCol, 0) where 0 means straight down.\n- Memoize pathsFromSplitter by splitter position.\n\nConstraints:\n- Language: TypeScript strict mode, ESM (use export, not module.exports)\n- No external dependencies (stdlib only)\n- Performance: must handle 200x200 grid with 50 splitters in under 5 seconds\n- Output ONLY the TypeScript code. No markdown fences. No explanation.\" -o text 2>&1)\necho \"$OUTPUT\"","description":"Delegate beam splitter implementation to Gemini CLI","timeout":60000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":634,"cache_read_input_tokens":20453,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":634},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc9625ab-c6cc-4fec-8128-ee6c97320ef7","uuid":"0d42d485-8716-4f27-8f1f-ea802c48fa13"}
